text.tspan: 4.1 The Buyer downloads each encrypted File Piece negotiated
in each Contract Section from the Seller(s).
4.2 Each Seller encodes a secret message to the PaySwarm Authority containing the
decryption Key for each File Piece. The secret message is placed into the Contract
Section. The Buyer will upload this secret message to the PaySwarm Authority when
they want to authorize payment and unlock each File Piece.
5.1 The Buyer digitally signs the Contract, authorizing payment for the
License. The Contract is uploaded to the PaySwarm Authority.
5.2 The PaySwarm Authority disburses money from the Buyer's
financial account into the License's royalty accounts.
6.1 The Buyer uploads each Contract Section to the PaySwarm
Authority, authorizing payment to each Seller.
6.2 The PaySwarm Authority disburses money from the Buyer's financial account
into the Seller financial accounts. The decryption Keys for each File Piece
are transferred to the Buyer in exchange for payment authorization.
7.1 The Buyer uses the decryption Keys to unlock each File Piece
and assemble the data stream into the final file that was
described in the Media and License.
